Ally Brazil (born 10 December 1958) is a Scottish former association football player, who played over 200 league games for Hibernian. He played in all three games of the marathon 1979 Scottish Cup Final, which Hibs lost in extra time of the second replay. His son, Alan Brazil, plays for Berwick Rangers as a striker.[1]
